o;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>1. Jacky Hunt-Broersma, a cancer survivor and amputee, sets world record by running 102 marathons in 102 days - She has documented all of her runs (and more) on her Instagram! It's @ncrunnerjacky</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/3QKt4cq.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>2. Black cat known for huge eyes, wonky feet to become mayor of Hell, Michigan. - Jinx the cat to become mayor of Hell, Michigan. This little black cat will rule over Hell, located about 20 miles northwest of Ann Arbor.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O7w39mx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>3. LeVar Burton, the beloved former Reading Rainbow host, will receive a Lifetime Achievement Award at the inaugural Children's and Family Emmys in December, the National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences announced this week.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ZDb4ME9.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>4. Plastic-eating Enzyme Could Eliminate Billions of Tons of Landfill Waste - An enzyme variant created by engineers and scientists at The University of Texas at Austin can break down environment-throttling plastics that typically take centuries to degrade in just a matter of hours to days. This discovery was published yesterday in Nature</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eU6RCrF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>5. US Army replaces cake it stole from Italian girl in 1945 - Meri Mion - who turns 90 on Friday - was 13 when her village of San Pietro, near Vicenza, saw fighting between US troops and German soldiers. Americans. Sgt Peter Wallis, who handed over the dessert, said it was "a little awkward" to replace the stolen goods, "but it makes me feel great".</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/eeWZbFM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>6. NAU to provide tuition-free college education for Arizona residents with household incomes at or below $65,000</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/HBDyfjx.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>7. EU reveals plans for the 'largest ever ban' on toxic chemicals - Thousands of potentially toxic or harmful chemicals still used in cosmetics, toys and even baby products could soon be banned in Europe under new regulations.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Gnk2FQy.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>That's it for this week :) Until next week, you can read my previous posts and subscribe here https://feelgoodnews.substack.com/ for a weekly collection of inspirational, feel good news stories from around the globe.</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/gXBtWbh</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[FeelGoodNews]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Fork, yeah!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/XCGrL9j</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RiBueu3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/XCGrL9j</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[PiercedViking]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Dying for nothing</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2UrqRk6</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/izC67RM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/2UrqRk6</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Srajo101]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Weird nerds for class hierarchy</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/6EtCLBI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/r6PG5uN.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/6EtCLBI</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[mugjunk]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Down from 300lbs to 173lbs in 18 months *WEIGHT LOSS PROGRESSION PHOTO UPDATE*</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/IR6H64y</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/U8wJPwA.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Boneless center cut pork chop seasoned with Penzey's Bavarian herb blend and pink salt, seared in ghee
Sauteed shallots, garlic and white mushrooms in ghee
5oz gently wilted spinach 
Blueberries
Nightly apple cider vinegar cocktail. 1tbsp ACV diluted in 2oz pedialyte and 12oz water

Workout notes:
Some pilates style stretching to warm the core and treadmill for 20minutes. 
I walked 2 dogs for 30 minutes each up hills in the woods at the shelter; Maggie and Tater Tot. Also, I cleaned 4 kennels for a total of 100 minutes volunteering. 
It's worth documenting that I'm feeling pooped going to the shelter after a good workout. Even though I eat recovery foods between the gym and the shelter, I have noticed that since quitting dairy 2 months ago that my energy levels are a bit unpredictable. I used to have an ounce or two of cheese in my recovery snacks and like 3 Chobani a day. 

Turns out dairy is very bad for my skin disease, Hidradenitis. I'm making all the moves to eventually get surgeries I desperately need. However, I have to raise a ton cash for the expenses not covered by insurance. I ask anyone who is inspired by my story to share my GoFundMe link in my imgur bio on your social media in hopes to get the medically necessary surgeries I need before I am a senior citizen! Insurance only covers so much https://imgur.com/user/tasteofnoise/about</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Azc4O1z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>As the economy tanks, grocery stores are reducing more and more perishable product. I got 1.18lbs of prime center cut pork chops for $2.62. Keep an eye out for reduced savings. Most grocery stores tend to markdown meat in the early morning while produce is often reduced in the evening. Ask the team members at your grocery store! I work in a grocery store so I go after SO MUCH reduced products.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/udf0Ur7.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sound on for a little ASMR if this qualifies. Look at that crust!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ANcj7Tv.jpg?1" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I decided to go through my posts and see where I was last year. 13 months ago I made my first progression post. https://imgur.com/gallery/f1e1N7D</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/RIGv8N8.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is about a week ago. I have shaved that monstrosity off my face since! This is the creepiest look I could muster for entertainment value.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/FauWiFT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Sorry, not sorry for the selfie. A shot of my temporary bridge; soon to get the permanent in a couple more weeks. Resolving the missing and broken teeth from being beaten by my half brother when I was 18 was a huge step towards my mental health recovery. I had to look at that trauma in the mirror for nearly 20 years. I've had so much head trauma in my early life I'm amazed I can tie my shoes.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/S9WbCme.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Secret Kitty Meeting Tax
As I was leaving the shelter I interrupted this meeting. Black and white kitty was shooting me daggers</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/00iNqu1.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>MAGGIE TAX! This is the current love of my life. Bitches come and go so often in my life now I'm having a hard time remembering all their names!

